msgid ""
"**Sentinel handling:** the source uses ``user_line_cap = -1`` to mean "
"“use the computed thermal limit”; we treat that explicitly rather than "
"via ``or``, which would select ``-1`` because it’s truthy in Python."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/ThailandPCM.ipynb:582
msgid "5. Per-station hydropower"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/ThailandPCM.ipynb:584
msgid ""
"PREP-SHOT models hydropower at the plant level with cascade physics "
"(water balance, head iteration, downstream-feeds-upstream water-delay). "
"The Thai dataset has 14 stations with full reservoir parameters: head, "
"coefficient, V_max/min, outflow_max/min, downstream link, delay hours."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/ThailandPCM.ipynb:586
#, python-format
msgid ""
"We ship the cascade as ``reservoir_water_delay_time.csv``, the static "
"parameters as their own CSVs, and the time-varying storage bounds as "
"``reservoir_storage_min.csv`` / ``reservoir_storage_max.csv`` (constant "
"across hours since the source has no time variation). Initial / final "
"storage levels default to 50 % of ``V_max`` — the same convention the "
"`SoutheastAsia <SoutheastAsia.ipynb>`__ example settled on for stable "
"rolling-horizon."
msgstr ""

