#: ../../source/ThailandPCM.ipynb:1079
msgid "9. Status and caveats"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/ThailandPCM.ipynb:1081
msgid ""
"The data conversion shown in this notebook produces a **valid** PREP-SHOT"
" scenario — the loader accepts every CSV and ``initialize_environment`` "
"returns a populated ``params`` dict."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/ThailandPCM.ipynb:1083
msgid ""
"On the current PREP-SHOT codebase, the LP build itself stalls in PoI’s "
"``make_tupledict`` Python-level iteration when the model is materialised "
"at this scale (472 zones × 212 techs). For a 24-hour window, "
"``create_model`` takes 20+ minutes before HiGHS even sees the LP — the "
"bottleneck is constraint construction, not the underlying solver."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/ThailandPCM.ipynb:1085
msgid "Two paths from here:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/ThailandPCM.ipynb:1087
msgid ""
"**Aggregate buses** to a smaller zone set before running. Defeats the no-"
"aggregation point, but makes the model tractable today."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/ThailandPCM.ipynb:1088
msgid ""
"**Accelerate constraint construction** in ``model.py`` / ``_model/*.py``:"
" Cython, Numba, or batched ``add_linear_constraint`` calls. The right "
"structural fix; would lift PREP-SHOT closer to PowNet / PyPSA scale-"
"handling."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/ThailandPCM.ipynb:1090
msgid ""
"Until either lands, this example is a **data-conversion artefact** — "
"useful as a recipe for plugging an external nodal PCM dataset into PREP-"
"SHOT’s input schema."
msgstr ""

